.SH NAME
devm_of_find_backlight \- find backlight for a device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct backlight_device *" devm_of_find_backlight
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function looks for a property named 'backlight' on the DT node
connected to \fIdev\fP and looks up the backlight device. The lookup is
device managed so the reference to the backlight device is automatically
dropped on driver detach.

A pointer to the backlight device if found.
Error pointer -EPROBE_DEFER if the DT property is set, but no backlight
device is found. NULL if there's no backlight property.
.SH "RETURN"
